11:11.001 --> 11:13.284
I gotta talk to you,
so I wanna see you.

11:13.319 --> 11:15.567
I wanna talk to you
about some stuff.

11:15.602 --> 11:16.985
- What stuff?
- Stuff.

11:17.020 --> 11:18.333
You know, I hate it

11:18.368 --> 11:19.767
when people say
they wanna talk,

11:19.802 --> 11:21.132
and then
they don't talk.

11:21.167 --> 11:23.400
Well, I don't wanna do this
over the phone, so...

11:23.435 --> 11:24.765
Just tell me what it is, okay?

11:24.800 --> 11:26.700
Otherwise I'm gonna be wondering
all night,

11:26.735 --> 11:28.233
and it's gonna drive me crazy,

11:28.268 --> 11:30.667
not that you don't have a lock
on that particular skill now.

11:30.702 --> 11:32.934
Why do you have to be
such an asshole?

11:32.969 --> 11:34.199
Practice.

11:34.234 --> 11:35.832
Yeah, you know what?

11:35.867 --> 11:38.467
Why don't you call and tell me
when you're gonna come see me,

11:38.502 --> 11:40.600
and, um, oh, yeah,
stop being such a dick!

11:40.635 --> 11:41.533
All right, listen--

11:44.934 --> 11:46.001
That's going well.

11:49.667 --> 11:51.201
Christ,
they're all blue.

11:53.001 --> 11:54.299
Hey, how's it goin', Tom?

11:54.334 --> 11:56.101
Hey, O'Brien.
What's goin' on?

11:56.136 --> 11:57.333
Ah, kids are all sick.

11:57.368 --> 11:59.368
I have to get, like,
a gallon of cough medicine.

11:59.403 --> 12:00.901
Really?
At least you can afford it.

12:02.301 --> 12:04.334
Did you quote my wife
$4800

12:04.369 --> 12:05.732
for a central-air unit?

12:05.767 --> 12:07.767
At those prices, I shoulda
gone into your business.

12:07.802 --> 12:09.468
What are you talkin' about?

12:09.503 --> 12:11.099
4800.
That's what you quoted.

12:11.134 --> 12:12.899
Are you nuts?
I never spoke to your wife.

12:12.934 --> 12:14.899
I don't even remember
the last time I saw her.

12:14.934 --> 12:17.134
Well, somebody at your office
must have quoted her that price.

12:17.169 --> 12:19.334
No, that would be me.
4800 for a central-air unit?

12:19.369 --> 12:20.432
That's what she said.

12:20.467 --> 12:22.565
Jeez, I charge
those prices,

12:22.600 --> 12:24.201
I'd be buyin' cough medicine
in the Riviera.

12:24.236 --> 12:26.134
Take it easy,
will ya?

12:26.169 --> 12:28.667
All right.

12:37.800 --> 12:38.765
Wow.

12:38.800 --> 12:40.067
That's a lot of food.

12:40.102 --> 12:41.299
Yeah, well, keep eatin'.

12:41.334 --> 12:43.368
The more you tuck away,
the less I will.

12:43.403 --> 12:45.800
Oh, you need juice.

12:45.835 --> 12:47.599
I'm good.

12:47.634 --> 12:49.465
You know, it's okay.

12:49.500 --> 12:52.101
You can eat if you wanna eat.
You know I don't mind.

12:52.136 --> 12:54.551
I know you don't.
You're sweet.

12:54.586 --> 12:56.932
You know, I've been thinking.

12:56.967 --> 12:58.767
I mean, I realize we've
only known each other

12:58.802 --> 13:00.866
- a short time...
- Yeah?

13:00.901 --> 13:03.967
But, uh, I don't know,
I thought we'd move in together.

13:05.934 --> 13:07.834
You mean, like,
you move in here?

13:07.869 --> 13:09.433
Or we could get a place.

13:09.468 --> 13:11.051
Are you asking me?

13:11.086 --> 13:12.599
I'm thinking about it.

13:12.634 --> 13:15.134
I thought
I'd just float it out there.

13:16.934 --> 13:18.334
I think we should talk about it.

13:18.369 --> 13:19.735
I don't think
we should go

13:19.770 --> 13:21.066
rushing into things,
you know?

13:21.101 --> 13:23.551
I mean,
how well do we know each other?

13:23.586 --> 13:26.001
I feel like I know you
pretty well, but...

13:26.036 --> 13:28.234
All right,
let's talk about it.

13:28.269 --> 13:30.799
I'm gonna be late.

13:30.834 --> 13:33.234
You're always
leaving me.

13:33.269 --> 13:34.498
I know.

13:34.533 --> 13:35.767
You know,
it's not fair.

13:35.802 --> 13:37.101
I'll call you later.

13:37.136 --> 13:38.334
Uh-huh.

14:10.301 --> 14:11.684
Theresa?

14:11.719 --> 14:12.993
You okay?

14:13.028 --> 14:14.233
Mike?

14:14.268 --> 14:15.634
Yeah. You okay?

14:15.669 --> 14:17.118
Yeah, I'm fine.

14:17.153 --> 14:18.567
Call me later.

14:20.101 --> 14:21.901
Okay.

14:25.467 --> 14:28.350
Grandma said
I can't have cereal.

14:28.385 --> 14:30.509
She said
it has lots of sugar in it.

14:30.544 --> 14:32.634
No, not lots, sweetie.
It's all sugar.

14:32.669 --> 14:34.084
That's what makes it so yummy.

14:34.119 --> 14:35.500
I wanna be a vegan
like Grandma.

14:36.500 --> 14:37.599
Oh, yeah?

14:37.634 --> 14:39.134
We'll talk about that later.
Eat up.

14:44.234 --> 14:45.301
Hey, sexy.

14:45.336 --> 14:46.333
Hey, baby.

14:46.368 --> 14:47.867
Come on in.
How are you?

14:50.268 --> 14:51.432
Mm.

14:51.467 --> 14:53.167
Hey, you know,
you're saving my life.

14:53.202 --> 14:54.500
I hope
you know that.

14:54.535 --> 14:55.599
I appreciate it.

14:55.634 --> 14:57.400
This is real strange.

14:57.435 --> 14:58.532
What is?

14:58.567 --> 15:00.133
Well, usually,
when I come over,

15:00.168 --> 15:01.700
I've got my clothes off
by now.

15:01.735 --> 15:03.899
Yeah, I know.

15:03.934 --> 15:06.384
Um, so did you, ah,
come up with any ideas?

15:06.419 --> 15:08.834
I thought I'd take her
shopping at Macy's...

15:08.869 --> 15:10.066
Good, good.

15:10.101 --> 15:12.400
and then the big Toys "R" Us
in Times Square.

15:12.435 --> 15:13.517
Oh, that sounds good.

15:13.552 --> 15:14.565
You owe me, brother.

15:14.600 --> 15:16.201
Yeah, and I'm gonna
start paying you back

15:16.236 --> 15:17.333
real soon.

15:17.368 --> 15:20.134
You should pay me back
right now.

15:20.169 --> 15:21.918
Oh! Hey!
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

15:21.953 --> 15:23.632
- What?
- Take it easy now.

15:23.667 --> 15:24.867
Not in front
of my kid, okay?

15:24.902 --> 15:26.067
It doesn't make any sense.

15:26.102 --> 15:27.266
I know.

15:27.301 --> 15:29.101
I mean, it raises all sorts
of questions here.

15:29.136 --> 15:30.518
I mean, why did she
even bother lying

15:30.553 --> 15:32.126
about talking
to this O'Brien guy?

15:32.161 --> 15:33.700
And what'd she do
with all the money?

15:33.735 --> 15:35.932
That too.
It's troubling.

15:35.967 --> 15:37.934
I mean, come on,
when a man lies--

15:37.969 --> 15:39.635
- Well, it's meaningless.
- Completely.

15:39.670 --> 15:41.668
We're genetically engineered
to lie.

15:41.703 --> 15:43.667
Absolutely.
I mean, it's like breathing.

15:43.702 --> 15:45.365
In with the air,
out with the lie.

15:45.400 --> 15:47.201
It's a timesaver,
when you think about it.

15:47.236 --> 15:48.599
Think of all
the long, drawn-out,

15:48.634 --> 15:50.267
idiotic conversations
you'd have to have

15:50.302 --> 15:51.901
if you had to tell the truth
all the time.

15:51.936 --> 15:52.899
Lying gets rid of that.

15:52.946 --> 15:54.919
- Gets rid of conflict, tension--
- High blood pressure.

15:54.967 --> 15:56.166
Not to mention cholesterol.

15:56.201 --> 15:58.334
Many, many bad things
disappear when you lie.

15:58.369 --> 15:59.734
See, but when a woman lies--

15:59.769 --> 16:00.866
I know.

16:00.901 --> 16:02.167
And Janet never lies.

16:02.202 --> 16:03.365
Never?

16:03.400 --> 16:05.450
She's like a freak of nature
that way.

16:05.485 --> 16:07.500
Yeah, well,
good luck with that, pal.

16:07.535 --> 16:08.632
Thanks.

16:08.667 --> 16:10.266
I must be
losing my mind.

16:10.301 --> 16:13.201
My bookie's runner comes
and meets me at the house,

16:13.236 --> 16:14.365
and he gives me this.

16:14.400 --> 16:15.767
Jesus, Mary,
mother of God.

16:15.802 --> 16:16.866
Holy shit. Wow.

16:16.901 --> 16:18.217
How much is in there?

16:18.252 --> 16:19.476
Sixty-six hundred.

16:19.511 --> 16:20.665
What'd you hit?

16:20.700 --> 16:21.799
The Seattle game last night.

16:21.834 --> 16:23.567
- Baseball or football?
- I never bet it.

16:23.602 --> 16:24.932
The guy screwed me
last week,

16:24.967 --> 16:27.400
and I swore I'd never bet
with him again, so I didn't.

16:27.435 --> 16:28.800
Maybe he felt bad
about what happened.

16:28.835 --> 16:30.568
He doesn't
feel.

16:30.603 --> 16:32.168
He's a bookie.

16:32.203 --> 16:33.699
I'm gonna keep it.

16:33.734 --> 16:34.699
- Yeah.
- Why the hell not?

16:34.734 --> 16:37.100
I mean, take Jeannie
to a show,

16:37.135 --> 16:39.018
some dinner,
buy the tickets.

16:39.053 --> 16:40.866
And you'll have
plenty left over

16:40.901 --> 16:42.784
- for more degenerate gambling.
- Exactly.

16:42.819 --> 16:44.667
I mean,
I've been betting with this guy

16:44.702 --> 16:45.632
for 20 years.

16:45.667 --> 16:46.999
He's never made a mistake.

16:47.034 --> 16:50.167
All of a sudden,
two in one week.

16:50.202 --> 16:51.701
What the hell is with that?

16:51.736 --> 16:53.201
Who cares?
Keep your score.

16:53.236 --> 16:54.201
You deserve it.

16:54.236 --> 16:55.233
Keep it.

16:55.268 --> 16:56.867
It all evens out
in the end anyways.

16:56.902 --> 16:58.001
Yeah.

17:01.500 --> 17:02.967
I guess I'll...

17:05.733 --> 17:07.699
No. No way.

17:07.733 --> 17:09.583
- Why not?
- It's never gonna happen.

17:09.617 --> 17:11.433
Did you not say
that I was--?

17:11.468 --> 17:12.397
Did you not say

17:12.433 --> 17:13.833
that I was
a really nice person

17:13.867 --> 17:15.251
and that you thought
I was cute

17:15.286 --> 17:16.560
and that I kept
in good shape?

17:16.595 --> 17:17.834
Did you not
say those things?

17:17.868 --> 17:19.531
That's not what I need,

17:19.567 --> 17:21.598
to get involved
with a firefighter on my crew.

17:21.634 --> 17:24.268
Yeah, that's gonna make my life
a hell of a lot easier.

17:24.303 --> 17:25.685
Who says
we gotta get involved?

17:25.720 --> 17:27.067
We just have dinner, drinks--

17:27.102 --> 17:28.701
No.

17:28.736 --> 17:30.435
Please?

17:30.470 --> 17:32.369
Don't beg.

17:32.404 --> 17:34.002
You're neat.

17:34.037 --> 17:35.600
Oh, my God.

17:36.867 --> 17:38.233
Listen,

17:38.268 --> 17:40.268
I didn't bust my butt
to get through probie school

17:40.303 --> 17:41.599
and survive my first house

17:41.634 --> 17:43.432
to come here and eat shit
every day

17:43.467 --> 17:45.299
just so I could be
your little girlfriend.

17:45.334 --> 17:47.817
I mean, that was never the goal,
believe it or not.

17:47.852 --> 17:50.301
I need you guys to think
of me as a firefighter,

17:50.336 --> 17:51.700
nothing more, nothing less.

17:51.735 --> 17:52.899
I'm really sorry.

17:52.934 --> 17:54.533
I get it. I get it. It's okay.

17:54.568 --> 17:55.734
Wanna make out a little?

17:55.769 --> 17:56.699
No!

17:56.734 --> 17:57.667
Okay. Jesus.

18:00.901 --> 18:01.901
How you doin'?

18:01.936 --> 18:03.099
Fine.

18:03.134 --> 18:04.934
I thought maybe
you wouldn't feel like going out

18:04.969 --> 18:07.268
- to eat tonight.
- Why not?

18:07.303 --> 18:08.665
This morning.

18:08.700 --> 18:10.634
You seemed pretty sick.

18:10.669 --> 18:11.599
Yeah.

18:11.634 --> 18:13.134
Well, I'm okay now.

18:13.169 --> 18:14.699
It was weird,

18:14.734 --> 18:17.734
because you didn't look sick,
and you didn't say anything.

18:17.769 --> 18:18.967
I'm bulimic.

18:19.002 --> 18:20.166
Huh?

18:20.201 --> 18:22.084
I have bulimia.

18:22.119 --> 18:23.932
What is that again?

18:23.967 --> 18:27.299
It's not really
dinner conversation,

18:27.334 --> 18:32.201
but, uh, it's a condition
where you eat and then purge.

18:33.767 --> 18:35.967
You make yourself
throw up.

18:36.002 --> 18:37.333
Wow.

18:37.368 --> 18:38.498
That's not healthy.

18:38.533 --> 18:39.767
It can't be good for you.

18:39.802 --> 18:40.799
Mike...

18:40.834 --> 18:42.667
do you have any idea
how huge I'd be

18:42.702 --> 18:43.999
if I didn't do this?

18:44.034 --> 18:46.368
Let me give you a visual aid.

18:46.403 --> 18:48.568
It can't be
that bad.

18:48.603 --> 18:50.699
This is me two years ago,

18:50.734 --> 18:53.001
before I started
throwing up.

18:56.767 --> 18:58.299
Um...

18:58.334 --> 18:59.465
that's you?

18:59.500 --> 19:01.467
They had to use
a panoramic camera

19:01.502 --> 19:03.401
to take that shot.

19:03.436 --> 19:05.468
How much did you--?

19:05.503 --> 19:07.500
Almost 400 pounds.

19:07.535 --> 19:09.166
So I, uh...

19:09.201 --> 19:12.032
I guess my question is now,

19:12.067 --> 19:15.700
you still think
I should stop purging?

19:15.735 --> 19:17.732
Hey, it's your life.

19:17.767 --> 19:19.134
Whatever works for you, right?

19:27.034 --> 19:28.617
- New York!
- New York!

19:28.652 --> 19:30.166
- Whoo!
- New York!

19:30.201 --> 19:32.634
Hey, wait. Tell me
what you guys did today.

19:32.669 --> 19:33.818
Did you see
any sights?

19:33.853 --> 19:34.932
- We came here.
- No, I mean,

19:34.967 --> 19:36.433
did you see
the Empire State Building--?

19:36.468 --> 19:38.299
We saw that.
On the way to the bar,

19:38.334 --> 19:40.034
you could see the top,
between the buildings.

19:40.069 --> 19:41.665
I took a picture.

19:41.700 --> 19:44.183
But this place--
This place is great.

19:44.218 --> 19:46.667
They got beers
from 72 countries,

19:46.702 --> 19:48.765
390 beers in all.

19:48.800 --> 19:50.532
Nothing like this in Fitchburg.

19:50.567 --> 19:52.450
If you drink one beer
from every country,

19:52.485 --> 19:54.334
- they put your name on a mug.
- I'm doin' it.

19:54.369 --> 19:57.500
Me too.
52 countries left.

19:57.535 --> 19:58.699
Bartender!

19:58.734 --> 20:00.632
Lithuania,
for everybody!

20:00.667 --> 20:04.167
Yeah! Lithuania for everybody. Whoo!

20:04.202 --> 20:05.599
I love
those Lithuanians.

20:05.634 --> 20:07.767
Seriously, what time are you
guys heading back tomorrow?

20:07.802 --> 20:09.901
Afternoon. We still gotta
put together the 9/11 tribute.

20:09.936 --> 20:11.401
You know, to honor
the guys you lost.

20:11.436 --> 20:12.832
We already have,
like, pictures--

20:12.867 --> 20:14.867
No, dude, we never made it
down to Ground Zero.

20:14.902 --> 20:16.400
This is our way
of remembering.

20:16.435 --> 20:17.398
Chuck made a banner.

20:17.433 --> 20:19.433
Oh, hey, Chuck,
that's really cool.

20:19.468 --> 20:22.000
- We want to do more than that.
- Yeah.

20:22.035 --> 20:24.533
We're thinking an eternal flame.

20:24.568 --> 20:26.765
An eternal what?

20:26.800 --> 20:28.001
An eternal flame,
like JFK has.

20:28.036 --> 20:31.099
It'll burn
forever.

20:31.134 --> 20:32.832
Well, that sounds
kinda complicated.

20:32.867 --> 20:35.533
We're still planning it out,
but we think it could be cool.

20:35.568 --> 20:36.765
Holy shit.

20:36.800 --> 20:38.365
Isn't that the guy
from your house?

20:38.400 --> 20:40.667
Yeah. He said he had a date
with his new girlfriend,

20:40.702 --> 20:42.268
but there's no way
that could be her.

20:42.303 --> 20:44.665
- Jesus.
- She's giant!

20:44.700 --> 20:46.301
Someone oughta pull
the harpoon out.

20:47.600 --> 20:49.934
That can't be.
I think I'm gonna puke.

20:54.034 --> 20:56.250
Holy shit.

20:56.285 --> 20:58.467
Oh, my God.

21:00.700 --> 21:02.201
What are you doin'?

21:02.236 --> 21:03.166
Nothing.

21:03.201 --> 21:04.167
What's with the joint?

21:05.167 --> 21:06.665
The one in your mouth.

21:06.700 --> 21:08.398
Oh, Teddy scored some pot today,

21:08.433 --> 21:10.234
and I didn't wanna be
a party pooper.

21:10.269 --> 21:12.067
I thought you were off the shit.

21:12.102 --> 21:13.817
It helps my eyesight.

21:13.852 --> 21:15.498
I took two puffs on this,

21:15.533 --> 21:18.099
and I seen things
I never seen before.

21:18.134 --> 21:20.901
Did you know that
Teddy's friend is a midget?

21:20.936 --> 21:22.334
Give me that.

21:23.533 --> 21:24.599
Sure, of course.

21:24.634 --> 21:26.565
You don't care
about my eyesight.

21:26.600 --> 21:28.400
You know, you brought me
the wrong drops, asshole.

21:28.435 --> 21:30.001
You know what?
I already got three kids.

21:30.036 --> 21:31.066
I don't need another one.

21:31.101 --> 21:32.450
You're like
a goddamn teenager.

21:32.485 --> 21:33.800
You know, I gotta
drive you around.

21:33.835 --> 21:35.201
I gotta pick stuff up
for you.

21:35.236 --> 21:36.568
It's a pain in the ass.

21:36.603 --> 21:38.168
I didn't ask
to come here.

21:38.203 --> 21:39.734
You want me out,
kick me out!

21:39.769 --> 21:40.734
Don't tempt me.

21:40.769 --> 21:41.799
Hey, Tom.

21:41.834 --> 21:43.099
- I made chili.
- No kiddin'.

21:43.134 --> 21:44.901
What'd you mix it with,
a goddamn shotgun?

21:44.936 --> 21:46.066
Don't worry about that.

21:46.101 --> 21:47.684
I'll clean the place up
spick-and-span.

21:47.719 --> 21:49.233
- Listen, about your cash.
- What cash?

21:49.268 --> 21:52.634
The 4800. We went out
to the track today.

21:52.669 --> 21:54.101
The little guy
wasn't feeling it.

21:54.136 --> 21:56.034
Don't call me little!

21:56.069 --> 21:57.333
Sorry.

21:57.368 --> 21:58.632
Sensitive little prick.

21:58.667 --> 22:00.132
We're going back out
tomorrow.

22:00.167 --> 22:02.167
Don't you worry. I'll get
him back in the groove.

22:02.202 --> 22:04.600
I'm gonna have my dinner
upstairs, okay?

22:04.635 --> 22:05.700
You gentlemen enjoy yourselves.

22:06.901 --> 22:08.368
And keep it down.

22:09.967 --> 22:10.967
Do you hear me?

22:11.002 --> 22:12.433
Yeah.

22:19.034 --> 22:22.301
Mel, it's me, Jerry Reilly.

22:22.336 --> 22:23.985
What do you want?

22:24.020 --> 22:25.599
I wanna talk to you.

22:25.634 --> 22:27.834
Look, as much as I'd like
to be a greedy prick,

22:27.869 --> 22:30.134
I think you made a mistake.

22:30.169 --> 22:31.665
Who is this?

22:31.700 --> 22:33.917
Jerry. Jerry Reilly.

22:33.952 --> 22:36.134
I'll be right down.

22:36.169 --> 22:37.201
Okay.

22:39.433 --> 22:40.632
How do you know
my father?

22:40.667 --> 22:43.467
What are--?
Oh, Mel's your old man.

22:43.502 --> 22:45.901
Yeah. Are you
a friend of his?

22:45.936 --> 22:47.565
Business associate.

22:47.600 --> 22:49.367
So he makes book
for you.

22:49.402 --> 22:51.134
You're not a cop, are you?

22:51.169 --> 22:52.233
No.

22:52.268 --> 22:53.500
- Jerry Reilly.
- Rick Pressman.

22:53.535 --> 22:54.866
Nice to meet you.

22:54.901 --> 22:58.301
